0.title: About Me

1.body: As far as programming tools go, I currently work using Knit , a framework/library created by Sleitnick by that allows me to work at a quick pace, and maintain a beautiful codebase. I program primarily inside Roblox Studio's code editor, although I'm capable of using Rojo and Sublime Text for clients that prefer version control. As far as designing terrain, animations, and UI, I prefer to conceptualize and do research using external programs, then assemble and polish the product inside studio.

2.body: Blender - I use Blender for designing animations. It's easy to use, and allows me to create higher quality work, while maintaining compatability. SyncSketch - Mainly used for animation analysis, allows me to plug in mp4s and analyze keyposes, extremes, and in-betweens. RigEdit Plus - Used for non mesh-deforming rigs.

Sublime Text - Awesome text editor, wrote this portfolio using it, enough said about it.
